<item>
            <title>[FLINK-22172] Fix the bug of shared resource among Python Operators of the same slot is not released</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-22172</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The problem was discussed here:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-20663?focusedCommentId=17317706&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel#comment-17317706&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-20663?focusedCommentId=17317706&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel#comment-17317706&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In general, the python process should be terminated when the shared resource is released as many times as requested. However, this reference counting logic has been implemented twice. Consequently, the shared resource may be requested multiple times but only released once.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
